"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-matteo-jorgenson-brandon-mcnulty-paris-nice\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Matteo Jorgenson became the third American to win Paris-Nice, while countryman Brandon McNulty took third for a landmark podium in U.S. men's road cycling history.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 163, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 16, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Jorgenson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matteo Jorgenson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Jorgenson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Jorgenson\"}, {\"begin\": 34, \"end\": 42, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.6997566430952208, \"rank\": 0.42877439488173985, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 79, \"end\": 94, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McNulty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brandon McNulty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McNulty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McNulty\"}, {\"begin\": 131, \"end\": 135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9877162863057418, \"rank\": 0.006838401701995874, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jorgenson, 24, won the storied eight-day stage race running down the heart of France, by 30 seconds over Belgian Remco Evenepoel.\", \"from\": 165, \"to\": 294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 243, \"end\": 249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9704613217133149, \"rank\": 0.01948079170129947, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 270, \"end\": 277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9622746198570838, \"rank\": 0.02157207037975993, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 278, \"end\": 293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Remco Evenepoel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Until this year, I never would have believed that this is possible,\\\" said Jorgenson, who resides in Nice.\", \"from\": 296, \"to\": 402, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 397, \"end\": 401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"score\": 0.9999999999390639, \"rank\": 6.114722166577585e-11, \"text\": \"Nice\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 25-year-old McNulty, who began Sunday in the lead, held on for third place.\", \"from\": 404, \"to\": 483, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 420, \"end\": 427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\", \"score\": 0.9999999991373443, \"rank\": 8.626470839703671e-10, \"text\": \"McNulty\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The pre-event favorites were Evenepoel, who owns a Grand Tour title (2022 Vuelta), plus world titles in the time trial (2023) and road race (2022).\", \"from\": 485, \"to\": 632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 536, \"end\": 546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Tour\", \"score\": 0.9999994110209542, \"rank\": 5.889794718559193e-07, \"text\": \"Grand Tour\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Tour\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Tour\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And Slovenian Primo\\u017e Rogli\\u010d, a three-time Vuelta a Espa\\u00f1a winner, the reigning Giro d'Italia champion and the 2020 Tour de France runner-up.\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 773, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 637, \"end\": 646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia\", \"score\": 0.9983331526060657, \"rank\": 0.0016283619875660964, \"text\": \"Slovenian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia\"}, {\"begin\": 647, \"end\": 660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Primo\\u017e_Rogli\\u010d\", \"score\": 0.9999999991191544, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Primo\\u017e Rogli\\u010d\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Primo\\u017e_Rogli\\u010d\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Primo\\u017e_Rogli\\u010d\"}, {\"begin\": 712, \"end\": 725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\", \"score\": 0.9999999994643076, \"rank\": 5.356537828320236e-10, \"text\": \"Giro d'Italia\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jorgenson and McNulty rose through the junior ranks together, sharing a coach and rooms while traveling Europe in their teens.\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 789, \"end\": 796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\", \"score\": 0.9999999991373443, \"rank\": 8.626470839703671e-10, \"text\": \"McNulty\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We both kind of saw that pro cycling was possible together,\\\" Jorgenson said Saturday.\", \"from\": 903, \"to\": 989, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris-Nice was not only the highlight of each's career thus far, but it was also an unprecedented result for U.S. men's road cycling.\", \"from\": 991, \"to\": 1124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 991, \"end\": 1001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Nice\", \"score\": 0.8313420322998837, \"rank\": 0.04320987654320691, \"text\": \"Paris-Nice\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Nice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Nice\"}, {\"begin\": 1100, \"end\": 1104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9877162863057418, \"rank\": 0.006838401701995874, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American men have never gone one-two or one-three in the three Grand Tours - Tour de France, Giro, Vuelta - nor at the Olympics, world championships or any of cycling's one-day monuments -- Milan-San Remo, Tour of Flanders, Paris-Roubaix, Li\\u00e8ge-Bastogne-Li\\u00e8ge and the Giro di Lombardia.\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1412, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1126, \"end\": 1134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.6997566430952208, \"rank\": 0.42877439488173985, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1316, \"end\": 1330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\\u2013San_Remo\", \"score\": 0.9637570188426524, \"rank\": 0.008209745762714191, \"text\": \"Milan-San Remo\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\\u2013San_Remo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\\u2013San_Remo\"}, {\"begin\": 1350, \"end\": 1363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\", \"score\": 0.9816675037644488, \"rank\": 0.004431782209560121, \"text\": \"Paris-Roubaix\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\"}, {\"begin\": 1365, \"end\": 1385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Li\\u00e8ge\\u2013Bastogne\\u2013Li\\u00e8ge\", \"score\": 0.9746117254733598, \"rank\": 0.016748768472911003, \"text\": \"Li\\u00e8ge-Bastogne-Li\\u00e8ge\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Li\\u00e8ge\\u2013Bastogne\\u2013Li\\u00e8ge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Li\\u00e8ge\\u2013Bastogne\\u2013Li\\u00e8ge\"}, {\"begin\": 1394, \"end\": 1411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_di_Lombardia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.481763040821897e-36, \"text\": \"Giro di Lombardia\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_di_Lombardia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_di_Lombardia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Americans previously won Paris-Nice (Bobby Julich in 2005 and Floyd Landis in 2006), but neither was joined on the podium by a countryman.\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1451, \"end\": 1463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobby_Julich\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bobby Julich\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobby_Julich\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobby_Julich\"}, {\"begin\": 1476, \"end\": 1488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Floyd_Landis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Floyd Landis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Floyd_Landis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Floyd_Landis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American women have experienced major one-twos: Connie Carpenter-Phinney and Rebecca Twigg in the first Olympic women's road race in 1984 and Megan Guarnier and Evelyn Stevens in the 2016 Giro.\", \"from\": 1554, \"to\": 1747, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1554, \"end\": 1562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.6997566430952208, \"rank\": 0.42877439488173985, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1602, \"end\": 1608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johnny_Appleseed\", \"score\": 0.9999966732512661, \"rank\": 2.203372972743917e-06, \"text\": \"Connie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johnny_Appleseed\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johnny_Appleseed\"}, {\"begin\": 1631, \"end\": 1644, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Twigg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rebecca Twigg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Twigg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Twigg\"}, {\"begin\": 1696, \"end\": 1710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Guarnier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Megan Guarnier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Guarnier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Guarnier\"}, {\"begin\": 1715, \"end\": 1729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evelyn_Paniagua_Stevens\", \"score\": 0.9999948913653931, \"rank\": 5.097264477446869e-06, \"text\": \"Evelyn Stevens\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", 